PORT ELIZABETH - Port Elizabeth police in the Eastern Cape are investigating a case of attempted murder after a man was shot several times on Monday in the cityâ€™s northern areas. Police spokesperson, Colonel Priscilla Naidu said it was alleged that a 31-year-old man was inside a shack in Hartebees Street in Helenvale when two men entered the yard and walked directly towards the structure. Naidu said several shots were fired through the door . She said the man was taken to hospital for treatment. No arrests have been made. The Provincial Organised Crime Investigation Unit is investigating a case of attempted murder. African News Agency (ANA)